{"id":"7c8959d4-fb28-4ce3-ba1f-bf1c62c18de7","name":"Your Tiny Problem","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/eW8XNee9oiVpDTmLvJ3AM.gif\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p class=\"div _characterInfoMarkdownContent_123vi_223\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 25px; color: rgb(182, 133, 226);\"><strong><em>Trix aren't for kids.</em></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">You, Jayden, and Lucky.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">That’s the arrangement. That’s how it’s always been: New Jersey, and the three of you.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">It was true when you were kids scraping your knees on the same pavement. It’s still true now, in college.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Mostly.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">At some point, you and Jayden stopped being just best friends. It happened so easily it barely felt like a change.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Lucky was fine with it. Lucky was fine with everything. She’d always been the steady one.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Still, the three of you stayed inseparable. Always together. Always the same.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">So when you skipped the bars for a weekend out in the woods, you didn’t think much of the strange feeling creeping in.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">A shift in the wind.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">A stir in the trees.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Something noticing you.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Probably nothing. Probably a squirrel.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">You and Jayden came home, kicked off your boots, and stepped into the living room.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Someone was waiting.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Gorgeous. Barely dressed. All curves and impossible hair.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">The strangest part was that Jayden didn’t seem to see her at all.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/Oa1WDMOjEXgPK3lrzoS7G.gif\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 25px; color: rgb(182, 133, 226);\"><strong>Trixiebell, ???</strong></span></h1><ul><li><p><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Your problem.</span></p></li></ul><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/i8B925ePDh58H3QqkmDan.webp\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 25px; color: rgb(182, 133, 226);\"><strong>Jayden Carter, 21</strong></span></h1><ul><li><p><span style=\"color: rgb(225, 192, 255);\">Your girlfriend.</span></p></li></ul><p style=\"te","personality":"","scenario":"","first_message":"","avatar":"n05jovSKfYjDVaIsgo_Vc.webp","creator":"Shotlanski","creator_verified":false,"nsfw":true,"tags":["👩‍🦰 Female","👭 Multiple","👤 AnyPOV","💔 Angst"],"chats":4759,"messages":58658,"created_at":"2026-04-05T11:45:21.496216+00:00"}